><span class=title>   Re: Raid planning and execution</span><hr size=1> Well raids are different depending on who you have there.  Everyone has their own method of doing things, and everyone will tell you that their way is better but the bottom line is you have to find what works for you and your guildmates.<br>
<br>
You can use the same raid method with 2 totally separate groups and end up with one being a total success and the other being a total failure. It all boils down to getting the people there to work as a team.<br>
<br>
There are a few basic things that run true on all raids tho:<br>
<br>
1) Main assist - make sure everyone at the raid is assisting one person - your enchanters will thank you for it.  Depending on the mob, you most likely want this person to be a warrior (because of defensive).  Make sure that your MA has a backup healer or some kind and make sure that if your main healer gets in trouble, he lets the rest of the guild know that he needs help keeping the MT alive.<br>
<br>
2) Secondary assist - pretty self explanatory - if your MA dies, this guy takes over.  Make sure that everyone knows who is the Secondary assist or you can have total chaos when the MA dies.  Also keep in mind that there will have to be aggro transfer, and fora short time there will be floating aggro.  This means that everyone needs to back off some to let the secondary get some aggro (specially your damage dealers)<br>
<br>
3) Offtank - this is generally needed on mobs that are unmezzable.  You overpull - you have 2 mobs running around and everyone is on the main mob - you want to make sure that someone is entertaining the other mob so that it doesnt go around picking off your healers, etc.<br>
<br>
4) Camping a cleric - Ok - you raid went bad - make sure that when you call the infamous &quot;Cleric Camp&quot; call, all of your clerics start camping.  This means that anyone who is not a cleric needs to rush in to combat to keep the mobs busy to give your clerics time to get out. Cleric need to camp - NOT /d.   Generally you can get one or two clerics out.  However, I have seen so many idiot melee, try to be save their own butts by camping as well, that all clerics end up slaugthered and no one gets out - then you end up with an ugly CR ahead of you.<br>
<br>
5) Consent - this is a personal pet peeve of mine.  I'm a rogue so naturally, CR is a big part of my job.  You say in guild &quot;everyone consent me&quot;.  You sneak down, and start dragging, sometimes stuff starts re-popping and when you have see invis mobs in the way it's a race against time.  There are always those select few who feel that a general guild message is not enough for them.  They need you to ask them several times, directly, before they will consent.  They are either too busy yapping, or just that clueless.  Nothing pisses off your CR team more than getting to a body and then trying to drag it to find out your don't have consent.  Then you wait there for another 5 minutes or so until they decided to finally consent you. It slows down the entire process.<br>
<br>
6) Pay attention - this is really what it boils down to. Most of the mistakes that happen in a raid are due to people not paying attention.  Someone was on the wrong mob, someone attacked too soon, the heal didn't come in fast enough, no one knew who the backup healer was, someone forgot to tash, etc.  Make sure that everyone knows their jobs and that everyone is paying attention =)<br>
